  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Health in Action</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building on significant and meaningful outcomes achieved in the health and nutritional status of thousands of school-age children during the program&apos;s first phase, this second phase of the project enhances and expands the program model to promote nutrition education, active and joyful play, and growing fresh foods. Program objectives include:

* Promote sustainable improvements in children&#x2019;s health and nutritional status through school-based participatory education and activities on nutrition, physical activity and healthy lifestyles.

* Improve children&#x2019;s nutrition by increasing access to fresh produce through the establishment of school gardens and the promotion of home and community gardens.

* Collaborate with partner organizations to increase children&#x2019;s participation in physical activity, both through school-based physical education and leisure time recreation and play, with an emphasis on making activity fun so that it becomes a habit.

* Strengthen parent involvement in education and activities to improve nutrition and adopt healthier lifestyles.

* Build the foundation for long-term sustainability by actively involving local and state government, academic institutions, other non-governmental and community-based organizations, and private-sector entities as partners in the implementation and ongoing support of the program.</narrative>
  </description>
